"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-team-gb-cycling-bikes-olympics-2024-b1175030.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  British Cycling's track bikes have been described as \\\"the best of British engineering talent\\\" with a view to \\\"working as one with the rider\\\".\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9945041248387546, \"rank\": 0.005284452020550312, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The design has been created in partnership Hope, Lotus and Renishaw, and is an evolution of the bike seen at the Tokyo Olympics rather than any sort of design revolution.\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 437, \"end\": 442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotus_Cars\", \"score\": 0.9976241693127719, \"rank\": 0.002324523040197979, \"text\": \"Lotus\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotus_Cars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotus_Cars\"}, {\"begin\": 447, \"end\": 455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renishaw_Hall\", \"score\": 0.9993452746826927, \"rank\": 0.0006551542627314167, \"text\": \"Renishaw\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renishaw_Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renishaw_Hall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the bike parts have been created using 3D printing withFormula 1-style technology.\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not a sense thatTeam GBhave somehow got the jump on their rivals in that regard - with the other powerhouses of the sport having taken similar approaches.\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But British bikes havealready crossed the line to one goldat theParis Olympicswith more set to follow in the coming days.\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9945041248387546, \"rank\": 0.005284452020550312, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bikes used between the sprint and endurance programmes are effectively the same, although the handlebars are wholly different when it comes to assuming the pursuing position.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The main area of change on the bikes is the seat post, which basically is split to create less disruption of airflow around the legs and therefore more aerodynamic.\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There had been tweaks to the handlebars too, which further enhances the riders' bike and body position, and there are new-for-Paris skinsuits.\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  The best destinations and activities to book this winter  Trying to work out the advantage the collective changes gives to British riders is hard to quantify but it starts with a psychological one according to six-time Olympic champion Chris Hoy.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1752, \"end\": 1759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9945041248387546, \"rank\": 0.005284452020550312, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Getting the skinsuits, the bikes, all the kit always felt to me like the final piece of the jigsaw,\\\" he recalls.\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1990, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was like an additional feel-good factor.\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You were in the form of your life, rested, fresh, tapered, this was just the latest in the culmination of all the pieces of the jigsaw.\\\"\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But he stresses this is not like Max Verstappen in a Red Bull and Alex Albon in a Williams in terms of the disparity of the technology.\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Verstappen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Max Verstappen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Verstappen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Verstappen\"}, {\"begin\": 2242, \"end\": 2252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Albon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Albon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Albon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Albon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Some people might say it's just like Formula 1 and it's the bikes win the medals but the answer to that is 'no',\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's part of the tools of the trade and you want the best tools you possibly can which is why teams invest.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And it's hard to say which team has the best.\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unless you line them all up with the same rider in a wind tunnel, you do not know.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus, the advantage of a nation's skinsuit can vary from one rider to the next with the different body shapes.\\\"\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  